body:
While investigation some issues in the Dart extension (https://github.com/Dart-Code/Dart-Code/issues/5668) I noticed some odd behaviour where tests are snapping back to their original locations when a file is dirty and VS Code was tracking changes.

I repro'd this with a gutted version of the test-provider-sample extension that just:

- Creates a test on every odd line number of a 20 line file
- Waits 10 seconds to allow you to modify the file (so that VS Code tracks the new test locations)
- Updates a single test location

When the test location is updated, all of the other tests in the file snap back to their original line number (losing the tracking that VS Code was doing). This seems unexpected. If the user is working on a file and adds a new test, we should be able to add/update it without all other test locations getting messed up until they save.


Video:

https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0786d5d9-073f-4112-8b66-4c2bd365c596


Repro code:

```ts
import * as vscode from 'vscode';

export async function activate(context: vscode.ExtensionContext) {
	const ctrl = vscode.tests.createTestController('mathTestController', 'Markdown Math');
	context.subscriptions.push(ctrl);

	const runHandler = (_request: vscode.TestRunRequest, _cancellation: vscode.CancellationToken) => { };
	ctrl.createRunProfile('Run Tests', vscode.TestRunProfileKind.Run, runHandler, true, undefined, true);

	const doc = vscode.workspace.textDocuments[0];
	for (let line = 1; line < 20; line += 2) {
		const item = ctrl.createTestItem(`test${line}`, `test${line}`, doc.uri);
		item.range = new vscode.Range(new vscode.Position(line, 0), new vscode.Position(line, 4));
		ctrl.items.add(item);
	}

	await vscode.window.withProgress(
		{
			location: vscode.ProgressLocation.Notification,
			title: "Will move one test, please modify the file first!",

		},
		async (progress) => {
			for (let i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
				progress.report({ message: `${10 - i}s remaining...`, increment: i * 10 });
				await new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, 1000));
			}
		}
	);

	// Move the test on line 11 to line 13
	ctrl.items.get("test11")!.range = new vscode.Range(new vscode.Position(13, 0), new vscode.Position(13, 4));
}
```

